Healthy charging – Step 1: Use constant current to perform fast charge up to 80%. Then select healthy charging to get a full charge.
Healthy charging – Step 2: Reduce charge current when almost fully charged. Then use impulse current to fully charge battery.
Healthy charging – Step 3: Use Trickle charge to keep electrons flowing inside the lithium battery, to make up for self-discharge and get longer battery life.
Turn on DU Battery Saver and start healthy charging when power is lower than 20%. It is advised to use healthy charging once a month to maintain the battery.
Turn on DU Battery Saver and start regular charging when power is more than 20%. It is advised to use this option on a regular basis to keep the phone in normal use.
